Expand description

This struct is used to build a mapping of external functions to their Prusti specifications (see extern_fn_map).

Fields

extern_fn_map: HashMap<ExternSpecDeclaration, DefId>

Maps real functions to Prusti-generated fake functions with specifications.

pub fn add_extern_fn(
    &mut self,
    fn_kind: FnKind<'tcx>,
    fn_decl: &'tcx FnDecl<'_>,
    body_id: BodyId,
    span: Span,
    id: HirId,
    extern_spec_kind: ExternSpecKind
)

Registers an external function specification. The arguments for this function are the same as arguments given to a function visit in an intravisit visitor.

In case of duplicates, the function is added to spec_duplicates, and will later (in check_duplicates) be reported as an error. Otherwise, the function is added to extern_fn_map.
